{"body": "@thedarkone @josh-lauer and I originally went with the `to_prepare` route but realized that it would only be fired when `.rb` files would be modified and not `.erb` files (or any other template files).\r\n\r\nInstead, we are directly checking for `config.action_view.cache_template_loading` (`ActionView::Resolver.caching` is set to the same value) before storing the the digest in the cache. The greatly eased testing, since the `caching` setting can be changed on the fly and not just at initialization.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/22140491", "created_at": "2013-08-05T20:57:59Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10791#issuecomment-22140491", "updated_at": "2013-08-05T20:57:59Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10791, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jridgewell", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/830bc5499b0658970c22ebf18d3bb36a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F3f098efb170e17387b60f08a6b406dbc.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/received_events", "gravatar_id": "830bc5499b0658970c22ebf18d3bb36a", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jridgewell", "type": "User", "id": 112982, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jridgewell/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237dbb8bd3543c1510088c9"}, "id": 22140491, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10791"}
